Here begynneth the Iustes of the moneth of Maye parfurnysshed [and] done by Charles brandon. Thomas knyuet. Gyles Capell, [and] Wyllyam Huffy. The .xxii. yere of the reygne of our souerayne lorde kynge Henry the seuenth. Suffolk, Charles Brandon, Duke of, d. 1545, attrib. name. Knyuet, Thomas, attrib. name. Capell, Gyles, attrib. name. Huffy, Wyllyam, attrib. name. Graye, Richard, Earl of Trent, attrib. name.
[20] p.
Wynkyn de Worde, [London : 1507?]
In verse. Imprint from STC. Caption title on A5 recto reads: Here begynneth the Iustes and tourney of [the] moneth of Iune parfurnysshed and done by Rycharde Graye erle of Kent, by Charles brandon w[ith] theyr two aydes agaynst all comers. The .xxii. yere of the reygne of our souerayne lorde kynge Henry [the] seuenth. Signatures: A⁶ B⁴. Reproduction of the original in the Pepys Library.
